==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pentamerous
<hw>Pen*tam"er*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Penta-</ets> + Gr. <?/ part.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>Divided into, or consisting of, five parts;
also, arranged in sets, with five parts in each set, as a flower with
five sepals, five petals, five, or twice five, stamens, and five
pistils.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Belonging to the
Pentamera.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pentamerus</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8
